United States: Repetition Mother of Wisdom
He even became comical, the diligent effort with which Barack Obama, president of the reputation of wise, replicated his predecessor's strategy on the Afghan question, which he himself considered to be very simple.
When he finally let his doctrine sweat so eagerly awaited, it turned out that he had copied it with carbon paper since Bush's Iraqi scenario three years ago.
Not content to use in the text even several times the expression "as in Iraq", he did not hesitate, moreover, to use the title of Bush's speech of January 2007 as the title of his own speech: "A new road forward"
At the same time, he personally criticized Bush's idea of sending new reinforcements to an Iraq consumed by the civil war as "irresponsible and a catastrophic decision in its consequences."
The following months, however, showed that Bush's strategy, which emanated from the recommendations of the campaign commanders, was the only one that could be so successful that the newspapers at the moment did not speak at all about Iraq.
This did not improve Bush's reputation, that being said, objectively speaking, he left his successor with a much more favourable final situation than one could expect.
Barack Obama hopes that in Afghanistan, the miracle will happen again
It was again the campaign commanders who called for an increase in the military contingent, including the Afghan Operation Commander, General Stanley McCristal, who even severely criticized the White House's reluctance despite the habits of subordination.
He asked for 40,000 men in order to make the situation more favourable.
The president hesitated for three months, but in the absence of a better option, he at least swindled the general of 10,000 soldiers.
He succeeded in extracting the promise of an additional 5,000 from Europe, even though he originally counted on 10,000.
What brings the most problems in Obama's entire strategy seems to be his intention to withdraw the armies from Afghanistan within 18 months and complete this whole process within three years. Obama's entire doctrine brings more questions than it provides answers.
Many doubt that an increase of half will bring the same results as the increase in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars of recent years, Iraqi society is relatively well organized and its leaders honour the agreements.
The Afghan situation stands out in the exact opposite - nobody can be counted on and no treaty is respected.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, accustomed to changing their day-to-day leadership according to what suits them.
The political institutions, although officially founded, will remain only a powder in the eyes behind which will proliferate patriarchal ethnic relations.
It is uniquely complex to balance the interests of the various ethnic groups in view of the lack of clarity about the relationship, which is still complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Even the foundation of a "quick state to act", which is the basic purpose of the operation, does not seem to be very real.
The time horizon of Obama's strategy is perplexed by his voluntarism.
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has worsened and is currently on the brink of chaos.
Only a purely romantic heart and out of reality can be convinced that the little soldiers sent into the tumult of war for their "prompt return home" will bring there a real miracle.
From a political point of view, defining a date for the withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible since the Taliban will regard it as the indirect admission of American defeat.
The latest NATO summit showed that Europeans' willingness to participate in military operations in Afghanistan is turning to the negative.
European politicians do not know or want to explain to their constituents how security in Germany or Italy is linked to a war in the Hindu Kush mountains.
Another factor capable of radically altering the situation is the evolution of events related to Iran.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and the reinforced sanctions do not affect the Iranians, the Americans will find themselves faced with the very difficult question of solving the problem through the use of military force.
This will have to be answered, for example, at a time when, according to Obama, America will come to the victorious withdrawal of troops from Afghanistan.
However, each such solution will lead to a dramatic reversal of the Afghan situation.
The only Russian for Obama is the fact that there are three years left until the presidential elections and therefore there is still enough time for him to work on a new strategy, in case it turns out to be a total fiasco.
